1) Recommending items based on global popularity can (check all that apply):
 
  a) provide person alization
  b) capture context (e.g., time of day)
  c) none of the above
  
  answer:- C 
  
2) Recommending items using a classi cation approach can (check all that apply):
    
    a) provide personalization
    b) capture context (e.g., time of day)
    c) none of the above
  
      Answer:-  a,b
  
3) Recommending items using a simple count based co-occurrence matrix can (check all that apply):
 
 a) provide personalization
 b) capture context (e.g., time of day)
 c) none of the above
   answer:- a

4) Recommending items using featurized matrix factorization can (check all that apply):
    a) provide personalization
    b) capture context (e.g., time of day)
    c) none of the above
   
         Answer:- a,b
    
5) Normalizing co-occurrence matrices is used primarily to account for:
a) people who purchased many items
b) items purchased by many people
c) eliminating rare products
d) none of the above
       
         Answer:= b
  
6) A store has 3 customers and 3 products. Below are the learned feature vectors for each user and
product. Based on this estimated model, which product would you recommend most highly to User
#2?
User ID Feature vector
1 (1.73, 0.01, 5.22)
2 (0.03, 4.41, 2.05)
3 (1.13, 0.89, 3.76)
Product ID Feature vector
1 (3.29, 3.44, 3.67)
2 (0.82, 9.71, 3.88)
3 (8.34, 1.72, 0.02)
a) Product #1
b) Product #2
c) Product #3
      
          Answer:-b

7) For the liked and recommended items displayed below, calculate the recall and round to 2 decimal
points. (As in the lesson, green squares indicate recommended items, magenta squares are liked
items. Items not recommended are grayed out for clarity.) Note: enter your answer in American
decimal format (e.g. enter 0.98, not 0,98)

         Answer:- 0.33 i.e- 1/3

8) For the liked and recommended items displayed below, calculate the precision and round to 2
decimal points. (As in the lesson, green squares indicate recommended items, magenta squares are
liked items. Items not recommended are grayed out for clarity.) Note: enter your answer in
American decimal format (e.g. enter 0.98, not 0,98)

           Answer:-0.25  i.e- 1/4

